<HEADLINE>
<P>
JEFF ALEXANDER; COMPOSER FOR FILMS AND TELEVISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeff Alexander, 79, a composer who scored more than 40 films and a dozen 
television shows, among them "The Tender Trap," "The Rounders," "Support Your 
Local Sheriff," "Dirty Dingus Magee," "Please Don't Eat the Daisies," "Julia," 
and such Elvis Presley pictures as "Jailhouse Rock," "Kid Galahad" and 
"Speedway." A former arranger for such big bands as Horace Heidt's, Alexander 
also did arrangements for radio shows including "Your Hit Parade" and "Amos 'n' 
Andy." 
</P>
<P>
Alexander, who primarily wrote or arranged background music, transitions 
between songs and other incidental music, was one of the founders of the Screen 
Composers Guild and served two terms on the board of governors of the Academy 
of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences. In Whidbey Island, Wash., on Dec. 23 of 
cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
