<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN FOUND SLAIN; 2 GANG SUSPECTS ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was found bludgeoned to death Monday in his Los Feliz apartment and 
police arrested two suspects, but one escaped, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Officers went to the man's apartment in the 4400 block of Ambrose Avenue 
shortly after 10 a.m. after stopping two suspects carrying identification with 
the victim's address, Detective Sam Jacobellis said. 
</P>
<P>
Anti-gang officers had stopped the car in which they were riding in a probe of 
gang activity. 
</P>
<P>
The victim's identity was not immediately released. He was believed to be in 
his 50s. 
</P>
<P>
Suspected gang members Herman Gonzalez, 27, and Robert Luna, 30, were arrested 
and booked on suspicion of murder at the Northeast Division station. But when 
detectives went to a holding area of the station to interview Gonzalez about 
12:30 p.m., they found he had escaped, police said. Details of his escape were 
not immediately clear. 
</P>
</TEXT>
