<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: LA JOLLA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By YOLANDA RODRIGUEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man died after falling from a cliff about 200 yards north of Scripps Pier, 
and a woman was in serious condition Monday after falling partway down while 
trying to reach him, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Marisa-Ann Ortiz, 21, and Jeffrey Alan Sardina, 22, had spent Sunday evening on 
the UC San Diego campus with a friend, Scott Douglas Simon, and the three ended 
up at the cliffs about 12:30 a.m., campus police said. 
</P>
<P>
Simon told campus police that, about 2:30 a.m., he tired and went to the car to 
sleep. He woke up about 4 a.m., just as Ortiz approached and said she could not 
find Sardina. 
</P>
<P>
Simon and Ortiz searched the cliff for about 20 minutes, then returned to the 
car. About 6 a.m., they searched the area again and spotted Sardina's body 
about 7 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Simon left to call the campus police, leaving Ortiz behind. 
</P>
<P>
When rescue workers arrived about 8:15 a.m., they saw Sardina's body, and Ortiz 
was found about 25 feet from the bottom of the 175-foot cliff. 
</P>
<P>
Capt. Allan Macdonald of the San Diego Fire Department said firefighters 
rappelled the cliff to reach the woman. 
</P>
<P>
Ortiz was taken by helicopter to Scripps Memorial Hospital, La Jolla. She was 
in the surgical intensive-care unit with a broken pelvis, internal injuries and 
cuts, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
George Dickason, county deputy coroner, said Sardina lived at 3048 Renault St., 
San Diego. An autopsy is pending. YOLANDA RODRIGUEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
