<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Michael Wynn of San Fernando High School made an oral commitment 
Monday to attend San Diego State University. 
</P>
<P>
Wynn, 6-feet-3, 205-pounds, said he also visited the University of Washington 
but cancelled trips to USC and Colorado. 
</P>
<P>
The fact that he has two cousins at SDSU -- redshirt freshmen George Glaze 
(defensive line) and Sebastian Glaze (linebacker) -- helped sway him, Wynn 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"I had insight into SDSU all season," Wynn said. "That made me feel more 
comfortable. I just didn't feel as comfortable at other schools." 
</P>
<P>
Wynn completed 53 of 140 passes (37.8%) last year for 726 yards and four 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State won all but the top two singles matches in defeating U.S. 
International, 7-2, in a nonconference match at USIU. The Gulls' Yoram Boran 
defeated Tole Marinkovic, 7-6, 6-2, in No. 1 singles, and Marc Shumacher downed 
Ricardo Herrera, 6-4, 6-0, in No. 2 singles. 
</P>
<P>
Joe McDonough won at No. 3 singles and teamed with Dax Peterson at No. 1 
doubles for SDSU, which was playing its opener. USIU fell to 3-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
