<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
IOWA DEFEATS NO. 11 ILLINOIS, 69-67 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Les Jepsen scored 18 points, including the winning layup with two seconds to 
play, as Iowa defeated No. 11 Illinois, 69-67, Monday night at Iowa City, Iowa. 
</P>
<P>
Iowa, which had lost seven of its past eight games, improved to 10-8 overall 
and 2-6 in the Big Ten Conference. Illinois, which has dropped 21 of its past 
24 games at Iowa City, fell to 15-4 and 5-4. 
</P>
<P>
Marcus Liberty scored eight consecutive points as the Illini opened a 56-52 
edge with 7:45 left. James Moses' basket brought Iowa within 58-56, but a 
basket by Irvin Small and a three-point shot by Steve Bardo helped increase 
Illinois' lead to 65-58 with 3:21 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Liberty scored the final Illinois basket with 1:44 left and Iowa chipped away 
at the lead. Four consecutive points by James Moses pulled the Hawkeyes within 
67-64 with 1:32 left. 
</P>
<P>
Wade Lookingbill made a three-point shot that tied the game with 35 seconds to 
go. Illinois missed three shots before Iowa grabbed a loose ball and called 
timeout to set up the winning play. Lookingbill sealed the victory by 
intercepting an inbounds pass with 1.5 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Lookingbill, Matt Bullard and Acie Earl each finished with 11 points. Liberty 
led the Illini with 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
No. 7 Syracuse 70, No. 18 St. John's 65 -- Billy Owens and Stephen Thompson 
each scored 22 points to lead the Orangemen in a Big East Conference game at 
New York. 
</P>
<P>
Syracuse (15-3, 6-3) never trailed in the game. 
</P>
<P>
Jayson Williams scored on a drive with 1:26 left to get the Redmen (17-5, 6-3) 
within 67-63, but the Orangemen made three of seven free throws. 
</P>
<P>
No. 10 Louisville 105, Southern Mississippi 88 -- Jerome Harmon scored 20 
points and Tony Kimbro had a season-high 17 points to lead the 10th-ranked 
Cardinals in a Metro Conference game at Louisville, Ky. 
</P>
<P>
Louisville (15-3, 5-1) shot 55% from the field and forced Southern Mississippi 
(11-7, 2-3) into a season-high 30 turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
Maryland 89, Virginia Tech 80 -- Tony Massenburg scored 25 points and Teyon 
McCoy 21 to lead the Terrapins (13-7) in a nonconference game at College Park, 
Md. 
</P>
<P>
DePaul 76, Miami 48 -- Stephen Howard scored 17 points and grabbed nine 
rebounds to lead the Blue Demons (12-9) in a nonconference game at Rosemont, 
Ill. 
</P>
</TEXT>
