<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRESNO STATE ROUTS SAN JOSE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wilbert Hooker scored 16 points to lead Fresno State to a 69-53 Big West 
Conference victory against San Jose State Monday night at Fresno. 
</P>
<P>
Tod Bernard added 15 points for Fresno State, which snapped a four-game losing 
streak and improved to 2-6 in conference and 7-10 overall. 
</P>
<P>
San Jose State fell to 2-7 and 5-13. 
</P>
<P>
Bernard had 14 of his points in the first half as Fresno State opened up a 
36-25 lead. San Jose State got as close as seven points in the second half, but 
a 16-4 Fresno State run broke the game open. 
</P>
<P>
Kenne Young led San Jose State with 14 points. Young's basket with 12:20 left 
in the game cut Fresno State's lead to 48-41, but the Spartans went almost five 
minutes without a basket before Mike Wasserburger hit a three-point shot. 
</P>
