NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Indian officials said that weightlifter Subrata kumar Paul, winner of two 
silver medals and one bronze medal in the 67.5-kilogram category at the 
Commonwealth Games in Auckland, New Zealand, was on his way home to Calcutta 
after being caught in random testing for use of an anabolic steroid. 
</P>
<P>
A second athlete who tested positive was not identified pending a second test. 
</P>
<P>
Later in Auckland, Australia's Glen Housman won the 1,500-meter freestyle swim 
in 14:55.25, short of the world record of 14:54.76 set by the Soviet Union's 
Vladimir Salnikov in 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
