<P>
Helmut Hoeflehner of Austria scored his second World Cup downhill victory in 
three days, and Steve Locher of Switzerland won his first World Cup race in the 
super-G at Val d'Isere, France. 
</P>
<P>
Hoeflehner scored his ninth World Cup downhill victory in 1:58.09, and Franz 
Heinz 1:59.24. 
</P>
<P>
Locher won by only 0.03 of second over Frenchman Armand Schiele, who was 
clocked in 1:32.16. 
</P>
