<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bank of New England to Sell Credit Card Business: Bank of New England Corp., 
strapped for cash because of financial losses, said it would sell its credit 
card business to Citicorp for $828 million. 
</P>
<P>
The Boston-based bank announced earlier this month that it was trying to sell 
$6 billion worth of assets. The bank has said it expects a loss of more than $1 
billion in 1989 because of bad real estate loans. The bank said it expected to 
make a profit of about $176 million from the sale of the credit card business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
