<TEXT>
<P>
Black &amp; Decker Corp., Towson, Md., has named Nolan D. Archibald, president 
and chief executive, to the additional position of chairman, succeeding Peter 
L. Scott. 
</P>
<P>
Archibald was chairman from December, 1986, until May, 1989, when Black &amp; 
Decker acquired Emhart Corp. Scott, formerly chairman of Emhart, was elected 
chairman of Black &amp; Decker at that time. Scott had agreed to serve as 
chairman through the post-merger transition period but had indicated that he 
would not stand for reelection. Scott remains a director and a member of the 
executive committee. 
</P>
