<P>
Going, Going: Lloyd Richards, dean of the Yale School of Drama and artistic 
director of the Yale Repertory Theatre since 1979, will leave both posts in 
June, 1991. The announcement was made Sunday by Benno C. Schmidt Jr., president 
of Yale University, who added that a faculty committee has been appointed to 
search for a successor. Richards, whose staging of August Wilson's "The Piano 
Lesson" is at the Doolittle Theatre in Hollywood, brought Wilson's work to 
national prominence while at Yale. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
