<P>
CRACK DEALER GETS 35 YEARS IN PRISON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man described by police as the biggest crack cocaine dealer in Oakland was 
sentenced to 35 years in federal prison. 
</P>
<P>
Darryl (Little D) Reed, 21, was convicted by a U.S. District Court jury of 
manufacturing and possessing with intent to distribute 28 pounds of crack, and 
of possessing with intent to distribute 15.4 pounds of powdered cocaine. Police 
estimated the drugs' street value at $3 million. Reed was sentenced here by 
U.S. District Judge Lowell Jensen, who chose a term midway between the 40 years 
recommended by prosecutors an the 30 years proposed by the defense. He also 
imposed a $50,000 fine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
