<P>
74 ARRESTED IN LAS VEGAS LABOR DEMONSTRATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Striking hotel workers briefly closed the main street downtown Monday night in 
a noisy sit-in that ended with the arrests of 74 demonstrators, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The strikers linked arms and sat in a circle in the middle of "Glitter Gulch" 
on Fremont Street near Binion's Horseshoe Club, where Culinary Union workers 
have struck in a contract dispute. 
</P>
<P>
About 30 police officers arrested the strikers after they refused to disband. 
There was no violence. 
</P>
