<P>
FIRE ERUPTS IN EMPTY CLASSROOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities evacuated students of the Travis Ranch Middle School in Yorba Linda 
on Monday when a fire broke out in an empty classroom. 
</P>
<P>
The blaze was quickly extinguished by the school's sprinkler system even before 
firefighters arrived. No one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
County Fire Department spokeswoman Maria Sabol said the fire began about 11:15 
a.m. in a home economics classroom in the building in the 5200 block of Via de 
la Escuela. 
</P>
<P>
The fire was contained in an area near a kitchen stove, leading investigators 
to believe that the stove was left on, she said. 
</P>
