<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
MAN, 74, ARRESTED IN DRUG RAID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Culminating a three-year investigation, local and federal authorities arrested 
a 74-year-old man and two residents of his luxurious Costa Mesa home for 
possession of methamphetamines, marijuana and explosives, authorities announced 
this morning. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested were homeowner Michael Patrick Marvich, 74; Tina Marie Anderson, 25, 
and Collin Lee Quick, 51, Costa Mesa police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police and U.S. Customs Service agents seized three kilograms of 
methamphetamines, 30 pounds of high-grade marijuana, a bomb, blasting caps and 
$23,000 in cash in a raid last Thursday, said Sgt. Tom Boylan of the Costa Mesa 
Police narcotics investigation unit. 
</P>
<P>
Boylan said it is unusual to find someone over the age of 60 involved in 
alleged drug trafficking. 
</P>
<P>
"We've had a few big-time drug dealers in their 50s," Boylan said. "But as far 
as I know, this is the first one we've had that is much older than that." 
Arraignment is pending for all three suspects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
