</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABC says more than 1 million fans have signed on as subscribers to a new 
magazine devoted to the network's daytime soap opera scene, about a month 
before the first issue is even due. 
</P>
<P>
The planned six-times-a-year magazine, Episodes, is promoted as being free, but 
subscribing actually costs viewers $3 for the cost of the phone call to sign 
up. (The number is 1-900-860-2600.) 
</P>
<P>
Containing articles about the stars and stories of just ABC's four daily 
serials ("Loving," "All My Children," "One Life to Live" and "General 
Hospital"), the first issue of Episodes is due to be mailed Feb. 20, according 
to editor and publisher Amy Dorn Kopelan. The network expects to reach an 
initial circulation of 1.5 million. 
