<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
MADER WINS SUPER GIANT SLALOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LES MENUIRES, France 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guenther Mader of Austria won a World Cup super giant slalom today, beating 
Norway's Ole Christian Furuseth by .45 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Mader was timed in 1 minute, 14.79 seconds to Furuseth's 1:15.24. Norway's Atle 
Skardaal, winner of the 50th anniversary Hahnenkamm downhill at Kitzbuhel, 
Austria, 10 days ago, was third in 1:15.26. 
</P>
<P>
It was the second victory of the season for Mader, who has won five times since 
his first win in 1986. 
</P>
</TEXT>
