<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
SOVIET LEADING WOMEN SKATERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LENINGRAD, Soviet Union 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Natalia Lebedeva of the Soviet Union took the lead in the women's competition 
in European Figure Skating Championships today with the top performance in the 
compulsory figures. 
</P>
<P>
Patricia Neske of West Germany, who was born and raised in California, was 
second and Natasha Skrabenevksaya of the Soviet Union third in the competition, 
which counts for 20% of the total mark. 
</P>
<P>
Lebedeva and Neske were second and third last year in the women's event behind 
Claudia Leistner of West Germany, who has since turned professional. 
</P>
<P>
The next portion for the women is the original program Wednesday afternoon, 
counting for 30%. The free program, worth 50%, is scheduled Thursday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
