<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
DECISION SOON ON CARDINAL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHOENIX 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cardinals could be just two interviews and a day or two away from having a 
new coach. 
</P>
<P>
General Manager Larry Wilson said Monday he will interview San Francisco 49ers 
offensive coordinator Mike Holmgren within the next couple of days. 
</P>
<P>
Holmgren, the last of several possibilities on Wilson's list, couldn't be 
interviewed until the Super Bowl was over. Now that the 49ers have won it, New 
York Jets General Manager Dick Steinberg also will be talking with Holmgren 
before Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
For Wilson, the Holmgren meeting is probably the next to last interview. Once 
that's done, he said, he'll meet with Cardinals owner Bill Bidwill "and the 
rest of our people," and then a second interview with someone on his list 
"could put it all together" by the end of the week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
