<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 ATHLETES FAIL DOPE TESTS, LOSE MEDALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AUCKLAND, New Zealand 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Weightlifters Subrata Kumar Paul of India and Ricky Chaplin of Wales failed 
dope tests at the Commonwealth Games and were stripped of their medals, 
officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
David Dixon, secretary of the Commonwealth Games Federation, said Chaplin, who 
won a gold medal in the 75-kilogram class, and Paul, who won two silvers and a 
bronze in the 67.5 category, both tested positive and have been thrown out of 
the games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
